Given my stated priorities — a career‑spanning, guitar‑forward compilation with punchy, distorted tones, strong low‑end and deliberate sequencing — ZZ Top – Greatest Hits best aligns with my tastes, while Essential Paul Simon emphasizes acoustic, vocal‑forward qualities and restrained production that run counter to my preferences.

